claim.claim-text:
1. A method, comprising:
building a network on a layer of a semiconductor chip;
determining one or more rules that govern placement of devices on the network;
creating, in conformance with the one or more rules, an electrical path on the layer between two adjacent metal traces that are both on the network,
wherein the step of creating an electrical path comprises placing a metal short on the network, wherein placement of the metal short decreases resistance and improves chip yield and reliability, and further comprises one of: connecting the metal short between end portions of the two adjacent metal traces, connecting the metal short between one metal trace and an end portion of an adjacent metal trace, and connecting one or more metal shorts along overlapping end portions of the metal traces; and
spacing the one or more metal shorts at pre-determined intervals.
